(26,'native plant cell','A plant cell that is either part of a multicellular whole plant in vivo or a unicellular organism in natura (i.e. part of a natural environment).','primary sporogenous cell','A native plant cell is formed by the division of the male archesporial initial. After several mitotic divisions these cells differentiate into pollen mother cells.'),
